<doc id="1079870" wikidata="Q8056732" url="?curid=1079870" title="You've Got to Believe in Something">
<text>You&#x27;ve Got to Believe in Something is the third studio album by American rock band Spin Doctors, released in 1996. It is their first album without founding guitarist Eric Schenkman who had left the band during the tour to support their previous studio effort. Schenkman was replaced by Anthony Krizan who co-wrote the album with the rest of the group. &quot;She Used to Be Mine&quot; was released as the first single. An excerpt from the song &quot;If Wishes Were Horses&quot; was used as the theme song for the sitcom &quot;Spin City&quot; in seasons 2 and 3.

