<doc id="1080059" wikidata="Q1727475" url="?curid=1080059" title="Lessig">
<text>Lessig is a German surname of Slavic origin. The original Sorbian form, &quot;Lěsnik&quot;, means either &quot;forest dweller&quot; or &quot;woodman&quot;, &quot;lěs&quot; meaning &quot;wood forest&quot;. Notable people with the surname include:

*Adolph Lessig (1869–1935), American union leader
*Lawrence Lessig (born 1961), American academic, attorney, and political activist

