<doc id="1080131" wikidata="Q8058038" url="?curid=1080131" title="Young Communist League of Sweden (Marxist–Leninists)">
<text>Young Communist League of Sweden (Marxist–Leninists) (in Swedish: &quot;Sveriges Kommunistiska Ungdomsförbund (marxist-leninisterna)&quot;) was the youth organization of the KFML(r)/KPML(r) during 1972–1978. As SKU(ml) was formed two front organizations of KFML(r), the Solidarity Front for the People of Indochina and Clarté (m-l) were merged into SKU(ml).

SKU(ml) published &quot;Ungkommunisten&quot; (Young Communist). It also had a publishing activity, called &quot;Ungkommunistens Förlag&quot;.

SKU(ml), as well as the party and other organizations close to it, was subject to political surveillance from SÄPO. In 1980 (by the time the youth league was disbanded) SÄPO had 203 individuals registered as SKU(ml) members.

