<doc id="1080164" wikidata="Q3533768" url="?curid=1080164" title="Monte Rosa tour">
<text>The Monte Rosa Tour is a circular hiking trail through the Swiss &amp; Italian Alps around Monte Rosa (4634m). The tour also encircles the Dom (4,545 m) in the Mischabel range.

Typical overnight stops are
* Zermatt
* Theodulpass (highest point: 3,301 m)
* St-Jacques in the Ayas valley
* Gressoney-La-Trinité
* Alagna Valsesia
* Macugnaga-Staffa
* Saas-Fee
* Grächen
* Europahütte

The section from Saas-Fee to Grächen is sometimes known as the Balfrin Höhenweg, or &quot;high path&quot;.

Grächen to Zermatt is along the &quot;Europaweg&quot;, and passes the Europa Hut.

